</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,870,1723]" box="[199,771,1410,1435]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1410,1435]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Host.</emphasis>
Collected on unidentified injured millipedes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,870,1723]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1446,1471]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</emphasis>
A noun from Latin meaning &quot;spike bearer&quot; referring to the sharp, ventrally pointed spike at the tip of the oviscape sternite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
